1604984400.title: Bargain Hunt
1604984400.descr: Natasha Raskin Sharp is in charge today as Bargain Hunt visits the Westpoint Arena near Exeter. Two sisters take on husband and wife as they race against the clock to buy three items in 60 minutes, with Danny Sebastian and Gary Pe keeping the red and blue teams on track. Meanwhile, Natasha learns about a mysterious book from the Far East.

1604987100.title: Bargain Hunt
1604987100.descr: Today's Bargain Hunt comes from Yorkshire's Elsecar Heritage Centre. Anita Manning leads the proceedings and she's joined by experts Kate Bliss and Jonathan Pratt. The reds and blues have the choice of an antiques centre as well as an antiques fair to find three items on a budget of £300. Fingers crossed they make themselves a profit at auction which today is with Knutsford auctioneer Nick Hall.

1604989800.title: Father Brown
1604989800.descr: Mark Williams, Mariah Gale, David Yelland, John Burton, Emer Kenny, Sorcha Cusack. Drama series based on the novels of GK Chesterton. Past and present collide when Father Brown investigates the macabre world of dollhouse crime scenes.

1604992500.title: Call the Midwife
1604992500.descr: Period drama series set in East London in the 1950s, following the life and work of a young midwife Jenny Lee and her colleagues at the Nonnatus House nursing convent. They serve the poor society of Poplar, London. Their main duty is to help bring safe birth to women and help them look after their newborns.

1604995200.title: Impossible
1604995200.descr: Entertaining and educational British quiz show, hosted by Rick Edwards, where 24 regular contestants compete throughout the series to answer tricky questions. But some of the optional answers are designed to be ''impossible'', or at the very least inconsistent with the information given. The participants must avoid selecting these booby trap answer and the best one wins the £10,000 jackpot.

1605038400.title: Scott & Bailey
1605038400.descr: Follow personal and professional lives of Detectives Janet Scott and Rachel Bailey, members of the Major Incident Team- MIT, within the fictional Manchester Metropolitan Police who solve difficult cases and fight crime whilst risking their lives on a daily basis in order to help those in need.

1605041100.title: Rillington Place
1605041100.descr: The shocking true story of the serial killer John Christie is retold in this compelling three-part drama series. Directed by Craig Viveiros, the series chronicles the life of Christie, beginning with the break out of WWII and up to his execution, revealing the toxic marriage with his wife Ethel and the relationship he had with neighbour Timothy Evans. Featuring performances from Tim Roth, Nico Mirallegro, Samantha Morton, Jodie Comer and Eiry Thomas.

1605044400.title: Friday Night Dinner
1605044400.descr: A family comedy about a Jewish family who meet for dinner every Friday night. The family includes mother Jackie, father Martin, and two sons Adam (Simon Bird) and Jonathan. The episodes consist of disruptions to the dinner by Adam and Jonathan arguing or by neighbor Jim Bell (Mark Heap.) It began just a year after the show The Inbetweeners finished, and worked as a new series for fans to watch.

1605045900.title: New Tricks
1605045900.descr: Popular long-running BBC crime drama about the trials and tribulations of aging officers as they attempt to solve the cold cases of yesteryear while coming to terms with their own years. Over the course of its 12 seasons it charted the work of the Metropolitan Police fictional unsolved crimes department, drawing its title from the adage of not being able to teach old dogs new tricks.
